      "Cloud Computing"
    ],
    "TSC Code": [
      "ICT-DIT-4020-1.1"
    ],
    "Topics": [
      "Topic 1: Assess Azure Cloud Computing Solutions (K1, K2, K3, A1, A2)",
      "Topic 2: Develop an Implementation plan for Azure Cloud Computing (K4, K5, K6, A3)",
      "Topic 3: Develop Review Processes for Azure Cloud Computing Implementation (K7, K8, K9, A4, A5)"
    ],
    "Learning Units": [
      "LU1: Introduction to Azure Cloud Computing",
      "LU2: Implementation Planning for Azure Cloud",
      "LU3: Review Processes for Azure Cloud Implementation"
    ]
  },
  "Assessment Methods": {
    "Assessment Methods": [
      "Written Assessment",
      "Practical Performance"
    ],
    "Amount of Practice Hours": "N.A.",
    "Course Outline": {
      "Learning Units": {
        "LU1": {
          "Description": [
            {
              "Topic": "Topic 1: Assess Azure Cloud Computing Solutions (K1, K2, K3, A1, A2)",
              "Details": [
                "Introduction to cloud computing",
                "Benefits of using cloud services",
                "Types of cloud service",
                "Core architectural components of Azure"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "LU2": {
          "Description": [
            {
              "Topic": "Topic 2: Develop an Implementation plan for Azure Cloud Computing (K4, K5, K6, A3)",
              "Details": [
                "Azure Virtual Machines, Containers and Functions",
                "Azure Virtual Networking and storage services",
                "Azure identity, access, and security"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "LU3": {
          "Description": [
            {
              "Topic": "Topic 3: Develop Review Processes for Azure Cloud Computing Implementation (K7, K8, K9, A4, A5)",
              "Details": [
                "Cost management in Azure",
                "Tools in Azure for governance and compliance",
                "Tools for managing and deploying Azure resources",
                "Monitoring tools in Azure",
                "Azure Resource Manager"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "Instructional Methods": [
    "Lecture",
    "Didactic Questioning",
    "Demonstration",
    "Practical"
  ],
  "Survey Responses": [
    {
      "What are the performance gaps in the industry?": "The industry faces significant challenges in effectively leveraging cloud solutions, leading to inefficiencies and missed opportunities. Many organizations struggle with understanding the requirements for cloud implementation, resulting in poorly designed systems that do not meet business needs. Additionally, there is a lack of standardized processes for assessing cloud performance, which can lead to inconsistent results and increased operational costs.",
      "Why do you think this WSQ course will address the training needs for the industry?": "This course provides essential knowledge on assessing cloud solutions, enabling participants to identify and address performance issues effectively. By developing a structured implementation plan, organizations can align their cloud strategies with business objectives, ultimately enhancing operational efficiency and reducing costs."
    },
    {
      "What are the performance gaps in the industry?": "A prevalent issue in the industry is the inadequate integration of existing systems with cloud computing components. This often leads to compatibility problems and hinders the full utilization of cloud capabilities. Furthermore, organizations frequently lack the necessary skills to conduct impact analysis, which is crucial for understanding the implications of cloud adoption on their operations.",
      "Why do you think this WSQ course will address the training needs for the industry?": "The course equips participants with the skills to draft specifications that address performance and security requirements, ensuring that cloud solutions are tailored to organizational needs. Additionally, it emphasizes the importance of aligning existing systems with cloud components, which can significantly improve integration and overall system performance."
    },
    {
      "What are the performance gaps in the industry?": "Many organizations in the industry experience difficulties in managing and monitoring their cloud resources effectively. This often results in unexpected costs and compliance issues. Additionally, there is a lack of established review processes to evaluate the success of cloud implementations, which can lead to unresolved issues and inefficiencies in resource management.",
      "Why do you think this WSQ course will address the training needs for the industry?": "By focusing on developing review processes, this course empowers participants to create metrics that evaluate cloud implementation success. Furthermore, it covers essential tools for governance and compliance, enabling organizations to manage their cloud resources effectively and mitigate potential risks."
    }
  ]
}

